cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with audio data collected from a passive monitoring sensor and focuses on detecting tonal vocalizations (whistles) of estuarine dolphins. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper involves processing of raw audio data to obtain spectrogram images and applying a probabilistic Hough transform algorithm to detect roughly linear ridges. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a system for automatic detection of dolphin whistles without interference of a human operator. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a random forest classifier to parse out false positives and achieve reliable classification of detected patterns. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper involves the use of image processing techniques to detect linear patterns (whistles) in spectrogram images.
